=head1 NAME

  Next-hop Determination 

=head1 Purpose

  Verify that a host properly determines the next hop.

=head1 References

[RFC 7084],W-3
[RFC 4861],Sections 3.1, 5.2 and 6.3.6

=head1 Resource Requirements

  * Packet generator
  * Monitor to capture packets

=head1 Test Setup

  Common Test Setup 1.2 is performed at the beginning of this test part.
  The Common Test Cleanup procedure is performed after each part.

=begin html

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<TABLE BORDER>
<Caption>Router Advertisement A</Caption>
<TR>
<TD>
	IPv6 Header<br>
	Next Header: 58<br>
	Source Address: TR1's Link-local Address<br>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>
	Router Advertisement<br>
	Router Lifetime: 600 seconds<br>
	Reachable Time: 0 seconds<br>
	Retransmit Interval: 1 second<br>
	Source Link-layer Option

</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<br>

<TABLE BORDER>
<Caption>Echo Request B</Caption>
<TR>
<TD>
        IPv6 Header<br>
        Next Header: 58<br>
        Source Address: TN1's off-link Global Address<br>
        Destination Address: CE-Router's Global Address
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>
	ICMPv6 Echo Request
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

=end html


=head1 Procedure

  1. TR1 transmits Router Advertisement A to the CE-Router.
  2. TN1 transmits Echo Request B to the CE-Router with a nexthop of TR1.
  3. Observe the packets transmitted by the CE-Router.

=head1 Observable Results

  Step 4:
  The CE-Router should transmit an Echo Reply to TN1's off-link global address using TR1 as it's
  next hop.

=head1 Possible Problems

  * None. 

=cut

